<paragraph blockId="35.[160,1156,142,341]" pageId="35" pageNumber="300">Body elongate, narrow, background colour white and semi-transparent with a central white circle on dorsum. Lateral body parts and foot with dark brown or purple colour. Cerata long, smooth; background colour green, with white spots, tip dark garnet in colour. Rhinophores smooth, large, with white dots concentrated at apexes. Oral tentacles wide and short.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="300" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="35.[160,1155,392,522]" box="[160,252,392,418]" pageId="35" pageNumber="300">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,252,392,418]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="300">Ecology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[160,1155,392,522]" pageId="35" pageNumber="300">
Specimens found in masses of the green alga 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="De Notaris" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[677,844,428,453]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Bryopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="35" pageNumber="300" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="duplex">
<emphasis box="[677,844,428,453]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="300">Bryopsis duplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, mating, and laying whitish and cylindrical egg masses at the base of the alga. This species can go completely unnoticed within the algal masses; moves actively at night.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="300" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="35.[160,1156,573,703]" box="[160,300,573,599]" pageId="35" pageNumber="300">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,300,573,599]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="300">Distribution</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[160,1156,573,703]" pageId="35" pageNumber="300">
Originally described from 
<collectingCountry box="[476,528,609,634]" name="Italy" pageId="35" pageNumber="300">Italy</collectingCountry>
: Genoa (
<bibRefCitation author="Trinchese S" box="[635,817,609,634]" pageId="35" pageNumber="300" pagination="10" refId="ref22834" refString="Trinchese S. 1874. Intorno ai generi Hermaeina e Acanthopsole. Memorie della Reale Accademia delle Scienze dell'Istituto di Bologna. 3: 10." type="journal article" year="1874">Trinchese 1874</bibRefCitation>
), Gulf of Naples (
<bibRefCitation author="Gascoigne T &amp; Sordi M" pageId="35" pageNumber="300" pagination="167 - 179" refId="ref19774" refString="Gascoigne T, Sordi M. 1980. A redescription of Placida viridis (Trinchese, 1873) (Gastropoda: Ascoglossa). J Conchol. 30: 167 - 179." type="journal article" year="1980">Gascoigne and Sordi 1980</bibRefCitation>
); also, 
<collectingCountry box="[432,531,644,669]" name="Portugal" pageId="35" pageNumber="300">Portugal</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Calado G &amp; Malaquias MAE &amp; Gavaia C &amp; Cervera JL &amp; Megina C &amp; Dayrat B &amp; Camacho Y &amp; Pola M &amp; Grande C" box="[548,768,644,669]" pageId="35" pageNumber="300" pagination="199 - 204" refId="ref18497" refString="Calado G, Malaquias MAE, Gavaia C, Cervera JL, Megina C, Dayrat B, Camacho Y, Pola M, Grande C. 2003. New data on opisthobranchs (Mollusca: Gastropoda) from the southwestern coast of Portugal. Boletin-Instituto Espanol de Oceanografia. 19: 199 - 204." type="journal article" year="2003">Calado et al. 2003</bibRefCitation>
); 
<collectingCountry box="[794,895,644,669]" name="Gibraltar" pageId="35" pageNumber="300">Gibraltar</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cervera JL &amp; Garcia-Gomez JC &amp; Ortea J" box="[912,1141,644,669]" pageId="35" pageNumber="300" pagination="215 - 224" refId="ref18719" refString="Cervera JL, Garcia-Gomez JC, Ortea J. 1988. Una nueva especie del genero Hermaea (Gastropoda: Opisthobranchia: Sacoglossa) y redescripcion de dos raros sacoglosos de la malacofauna europea. Iberus. 8: 215 - 224." type="journal article" year="1988">Cervera et al. 1988</bibRefCitation>
); 
<collectingCountry box="[160,227,678,703]" name="Spain" pageId="35" pageNumber="300">Spain</collectingCountry>
: Andalusian coast (this study), 
<collectingRegion box="[604,713,678,703]" country="Spain" name="Catalunya" pageId="35" pageNumber="300">Catalonia</collectingRegion>
(this study); 
<collectingCountry box="[874,951,678,703]" name="France" pageId="35" pageNumber="300">France</collectingCountry>
(this study).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="300" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="35.[159,1155,770,900]" box="[160,262,770,796]" pageId="35" pageNumber="300">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,262,770,796]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="300">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[159,1155,770,900]" pageId="35" pageNumber="300">
This species can be misidentified as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Trinchese, 1874)" baseAuthorityName="Trinchese" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[551,826,806,831]" class="Gastropoda" family="Limapontiidae" genus="Placida" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="35" pageNumber="300" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="vidiris">
<emphasis box="[551,637,806,831]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="300">P. vidiris</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Trinchese S" box="[649,818,806,831]" pageId="35" pageNumber="300" pagination="10" refId="ref22834" refString="Trinchese S. 1874. Intorno ai generi Hermaeina e Acanthopsole. Memorie della Reale Accademia delle Scienze dell'Istituto di Bologna. 3: 10." type="journal article" year="1874">Trinchese, 1874</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but it is distinguishable by its brown or purple body margins and the tip of the cerata darkly coloured in garnet (
<bibRefCitation author="Pruvot-Fol A" pageId="35" pageNumber="300" refId="ref22007" refString="Pruvot-Fol A. 1954. Faune de France. Mollusques Opisthobranches 58. Paris: Paul Lechevalier" type="book" year="1954">Pruvot-Fol 1954</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
